<P>
   TAX-REVENUES _ LAS VEGAS _ Awash in money, state governments
across America are slashing taxes and piling up reserves in
economic times that haven't been this good in almost 20 years. News
of the increasing flow of money into state coffers came Tuesday at
the annual meeting of the National Conference of State Legislatures
being held, fittingly perhaps, in the city where money is king. By
KEVIN MURPHY. Story will move in ``a'' category.
