r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MURDER-AZR &LR;      07-23 0639
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MURDER-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PAIR TRIED TO SELL `SERIAL KILLER' TALE; NOW WOMAN FACES MURDER
CHARGE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By CHRISTINA LEONARD  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Last week, Russell and Dominique Keys tried in vain to sell the
tabloids a lurid story about Russell being a British serial killer.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, Dominique Keys sat in a Maricopa County jail
facing first-degree murder charges for reportedly killing her
husband.
</P>
<P>
   Dominique, 54, was arrested Tuesday afternoon after police say
she fatally shot 40-year-old Russell at a friend's house near 30th
Street and McDowell Road in Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   The woman told police her husband had earlier confessed to
murdering five women in England. In fact, the couple had tried to
sell the story to two tabloids: Florida-based ``National Examiner''
and London's ``Sun,'' Phoenix police Detective Frank DiModica said.
</P>
<P>
   However, police are treating the case as a domestic violence
related homicide.
</P>
<P>
   ``What happened in England is something that really isn't a
factor in this investigation right now,'' DiModica said.
</P>
<P>
   Brian Williams, editor of ``National Examiner,'' said Wednesday
that Russell called the Florida-based tabloid from Phoenix this
week claiming he was a serial killer.
</P>
<P>
   ``He talked to a reporter for a fair amount of time,'' Williams
said. ``It was a rather detailed interview.''
</P>
<P>
   Williams said the tabloid didn't pay for the story because it
could not immediately confirm the facts; the couple and the tabloid
never negotiated a deal. However, ``National Examiner'' plans to
run a story at the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a preposterous story to begin with,'' the editor said.
``It needed a lot of checking out.``
</P>
<P>
   Williams said Dominique was ``obviously concerned'' about her
husband's alleged behavior and wanted to turn him in to law
enforcement. However, Russell told the tabloid that he had tried to
surrender himself once in England, but police did not believe him.
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman with the police department in Blackpool, England,
would say little about Russell Keys on Wednesday, but acknowledged
its contact with him.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can confirm that Mr. Keys was interviewed by officers at
Blackpool police station on the 26th of June this year in
connection with information regarding possible serious offenses in
Lancashire and elsewhere,'' according to a department statement.
``Extensive inquiries were made at that time, which failed to
corroborate any of the information the police have received.
</P>
<P>
   ``Mr. Keys was released, and at the time of his death no
proceedings have been instigated against him nor were any
anticipated.''
</P>
<P>
   According to court documents, the couple recently moved to
Arizona from Stroud, Gloucestershire, which is about 100 miles from
London.
</P>
<P>
   Dominique, who is a U.S. citizen, told police that she and her
husband were arguing Tuesday afternoon at the home of a friend,
Paul Gilligan, when her husband came at her as if to choke her.
</P>
<P>
   She pushed him away, and when he tried to attack her again, she
grabbed a loaded 9mm handgun from a duffel bag, which she had
bought that day for protection ``because she lived in a bad
neighborhood,'' according to the documents.
</P>
<P>
   Gilligan, who called 911, told police he was in the bedroom when
the shooting occurred: ``She's sitting here talking to him,
standing here talking to him _ screaming at him,'' according to the
911 tape.
</P>
<P>
   Gilligan told police that he is a friend of Dominique Keys and
allowed the couple to stay at his home. He could not be reached for
comment Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Dominique had no visible signs of trauma or evidence
she was attacked by her husband. She was being held in lieu of
$450,000 bail.  &QL; 
 &UR; tagChristina Leonard can be reached at 444-8995 or at christina.
 &UR; leonard &LR; pni.com via e-mail. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
