actor involves much work, discipline and a permanent search for
financial backing. Fame comes at the very end ..... By Claudia
Weidlich. 1,500 words. B. The School of Hard Knocks : Martial arts
are growing in popularity in Europe, but is the sport staying true
to its roots? By Jahnnabi Das. 1,500 words. 7. WHAT'S DOING IN
TORONTO Toronto has never been a bigger attraction than it is right
now. Here are ideas on events, sightseeing, hotels and restaurants
in this busy and bright Canadian city. By Anthony DePalma. New York
Times Way To Go! 1,800 words. 8. CHILD RAPE IN SOUTH AFRICA It is
tragically common to find the young, vulnerable and violated in the
new South Africa. In this nation that might have the highest
incidence of rape in the world, children are becoming a primary
target. By Suzanne Daley. From The New York Times Magazine. 1,000
words.
_______________________________________________________________ 9.
THE PROMISE OF ONE TO ONE (A LOVE STORY) The honeymoon is over.
