<HEADLINE>
ATTN EDITORS:  

</HEADLINE>
  
 For Immediate Release
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; The inside story of the FBI's two-decade entanglement with
James ``Whitey'' Bulger and Stephen ``The Rifleman'' Flemmi can now
be told as a result of extraordinary court hearings in Boston to
determine whether the 1995 indictments against the pair should be
dismissed. Information obtained by the Globe paints a portrait of
some of the nation's most elite crime fighters working in collusion
with two of the region's top gangsters. The five-part series was
prepared and written by Globe Spotlight Team editor Gerard O'Neill
and reporters Dick Lehr, Mitchell Zuckoff and Shelley Murphy. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MOB-I-SPCL (Boston) -- James ``Whitey'' Bulger and FBI agent
John Connolly join forces, creating a bond that benefits both their
careers. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-LIES-SPCL (Boston) -- The way former FBI agent John Connolly
sees it, several of his onetime colleagues have lied about him
under oath. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-MYTHS-SPCL (Boston) -- With the release of once-secret FBI
files, two decades of Bulger mythology have unraveled. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOB-II-SPCL (Boston) -- The FBI claims Bulger played a key role
in destroying the Angiulo Mafia family in Boston. But is it true?
(2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-FLEMMI-SPCL (Boston) -- In many ways, the soft-spoken Stehen
``The Rifleman'' Flemmi was the main man while he operated in the
shadows. 1400 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOB-III-SPCL (Boston) -- Inside the FBI, agent John Connolly
repeatedly embellishes James ``Whitey'' Bulger's worth. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-WHITEY-SPCL (Boston) -- Whitey Bulger is no longer the boss
of South Boston, the man whose very name instilled fear and awe. By
Dick Lehr. 950 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOB-IV-SPCL (Boston) -- With the FBI in their corner, Bulger and
partner Stephen Flemmi run rackets _ and more _ with impunity. (2
takes)
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-MORE-LIES-SPCL (Boston) -- Comments by law enforcement
officials a decade ago are now sharply contradicted by this year's
release of FBI files and court testimony. 400 words.
</P>
<P>
   w/
</P>
<P>
   MOB-WINTER-SPCL (Boston) -- Howie Winter, who was replaced by
Whitey Bulger as head of the Winter Hill gang, says ``no way'' did
he ever suspect that Bulger was an FBI informant. By Shelley
Murphy. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOB-V-SPCL (Boston) -- The ``Town'' tolerated Bulger in the
belief that he kept drug dealers at bay. But Bulger broke the
bargain. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
