</P>
<P>
   Ion channels in a neighboring cell sense the electron discharge
and open, allowing sodium ions to rush in. This, in turn, changes
the charge within that cell, causing it to unleash a storm of
electrons to its neighbor.
</P>
<P>
   Its a domino effect that happens so fast that the electrical
