<SLUG> BC-SHARP-DRIVING24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Cars like TDI Jetta deserve a second look
 &HT;    By Linda Sharp
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- Bob and Tony are in sales, and they travel a great
deal. Bob normally drives an extended-cab four-wheel-drive pickup,
Tony a two-door sport-utility vehicle. Both are pretty big men.
</P>
<P>
   Recently their boss told them they would be taking an extended
sales trip together. Their route would take them from Atlanta to
Davenport, Iowa, on to Minneapolis and then back to Atlanta. To
make their trip more pleasurable, he was providing them with the
newest company vehicle, a Volkswagen TDI Jetta.
</P>
<P>
   These two burly types would be taking an almost 3,000-mile trip
in a Volkswagen -- with a diesel engine, no less. Their boss
assured them the VW would be up to the task.
</P>
<P>
   Bob and Tony approached their new ride with more than just a bit
of skepticism. Before them sat what appeared to be a small
four-door econobox. They said, ``We'll get out of this. There's no
way we will ever get all our supplies in this little car.''
</P>
<P>
   Then they opened the cavernous trunk. Not only did it hold all
their product and luggage, they actually tossed in a couple of golf
bags, just in case. To their surprise, they found the front seat
area to be more than ample for their full figures.
</P>
<P>
   All they had left to complain about was the Jetta's diesel
engine.
</P>
<P>
   Bob barked, ``With all this stuff and us, this thing will
probably never get over Monteagle outside of Chattanooga.''
</P>
<P>
   Reports are that not only did the Jetta scale Monteagle, it did
it in excess of the speed limit.
</P>
<P>
   Their trip was just over 3,200 miles, but their total fuel bill
was just under $75. The accounting department actually questioned
the correctness of their mileage.
</P>
<P>
   If you are a commuter who travels 50 miles a day, gets an
average of 20 mpg at an average price of $1 per gallon, your annual
fuel cost would be $650. The Jetta TDI averaged about 48 mpg on
Tony and Bob's trip. The annual fuel cost on the TDI-equipped Jetta
would be only about $270. With a range of more than 600 miles per
tankful, you would probably only have to fill up every two weeks.
</P>
<P>
   Diesel engines are standard fare in European markets, where fuel
often costs more than $3.50 per gallon.
</P>
<P>
   Americans are still in the learning process about diesels. VW's
TDI is one of the best around. No noise, no smoke and, because of
turbocharging, great acceleration. Another big benefit is they
produce 20 percent less carbon dioxide than a gasoline motor.
</P>
<P>
   One look at Atlanta or any other metropolitan area's skyline on
a muggy summer day, many commuters may agree the diesel's time may
have come.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
