<HEADER>
A9041 &Cx1f; tad-z
r d &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-SALAD-SIDE24-COX     07-23 0656
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SALAD-SIDE24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Easy salad recipes help take the sizzle out of summer meals
 &HT;    By Jan Norris
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Takeout is our first choice for quick, cool summer meals, but if
you're going to make your own, keep it simple. The most you should
do is boil pasta, as for the first recipe by Marcel Desaulniers.
The recipe is featured in his new book, ``Salad Days'' (Simon &AMP;
Schuster, $27.50.) Note that the recipes in the book, while
inspired, are lengthy and involve several steps.
</P>
<P>
   Penne pasta and spinach with cracked black pepper vinaigrette
</P>
<P>
   For the oven-roasted plum tomatoes:
</P>
<P>
   12 medium plum tomatoes, washed and cored
</P>
<P>
   Salt and freshly ground black pepper
</P>
<P>
   For the cracked black pepper vinaigrette:
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons cider vinegar
</P>
<P>
   4 tablespoons fresh lemon juice
</P>
<P>
   2 teaspoons freshly cracked black peppercorns
</P>
<P>
   1 teaspoon salt
</P>
<P>
   3/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil
</P>
<P>
   For pasta:
</P>
<P>
   1 pound penne pasta, cooked, drained
</P>
<P>
   Vinaigrette (above)
</P>
<P>
   3/4 pound flat-leaf spinach, stemmed, washed, cut into strips
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper to taste
</P>
<P>
   For greens and garnish:
</P>
<P>
   1 cup walnuts, broken, toasted
</P>
<P>
   3/4 pound curly endive, cored, trimmed, cut into 3/4-inch
pieces, washed and dried
</P>
<P>
   To roast the plum tomatoes, preheat oven to 225 degrees. Cut
each tomato in half lengthwise, then cut each half into 2 sections
lengthwise. Place tomatoes, skin side down, on a baking sheet lined
with parchment paper. Season lightly with salt and pepper. Place
tomatoes in preheated oven and roast for 3 hours. Remove and cool
to room temperature. (The tomatoes can be kept at room temperature
for 3 to 4 hours, until ready to use, or stored in a tightly sealed
plastic container in the refrigerator for several days.)
</P>
<P>
   To make the vinaigrette: In a 3-quart stainless steel bowl,
whisk together the cider vinegar, lemon juice, peppercorns, and
salt. Add olive oil in a slow, steady stream while whisking t the
tough stems of the asparagus stalks. In a 3-quart saucepan, heat
the asparagus and enough water to cover to boiling over high heat.
Reduce heat to medium and cook only for 1 minute. Drain in a
colander and set aside to cool to room temperature.
</P>
<P>
   In a blender, combine oil, vinegar, raspberries, sugar and salt
till combined.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, arrange 3 stalks of asparagus side by side on each of
4 serving plates. Place one slice of turkey on top of the asparagus
on each plate with 1 cup of salad greens.
</P>
<P>
   Divide fresh raspberries among the serving plates and sprinkle
with some of the flower petals, if desired. Pulse the vinaigrette
several times in the blender and pour over the salad.
</P>
<P>
   Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   SHRIMP AND MELON SALAD
</P>
<P>
   3 tablespoons peanut oil
</P>
<P>
   1 pound large shrimp, peeled and deveined
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon finely chopped peeled fresh ginger
</P>
<P>
   2 cups (1 inch pieces) mixed melon
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup fresh lime juice
</P>
<P>
   2 green onions, thinly sliced
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sugar
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon sesame oil
</P>
<P>
   1 tablespoon soy sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/4 teaspoon hot red-pepper sauce
</P>
<P>
   4 leaves green-leaf lettuce
</P>
<P>
   4 leaves red-leaf lettuce
</P>
<P>
   In a large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon peanut oil over medium
heat. Add shrimp and ginger. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
shrimp are pink and cooked through _ 4 to 5 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Transfer the shrimp mixture to a large bowl. Stir in the melons,
lime juice, green onions, remaining peanut oil, sugar, sesame oil,
soy and red-pepper sauce.
</P>
<P>
   Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until cold _ at
least 1 hour.
</P>
<P>
   To serve, arrange lettuce around the edge of a chilled serving
platter. Use a slotted spoon to stir the shrimp and melon mixture
and spoon into the center of the lettuce. Serve the lime-juice
mixture that remains in the shrimp bowl as the dressing with the
salad. Makes 4 servings.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
