<P>
   GOLDEN-ANNIVERSARIES _ It's the golden age of the golden
anniversary, thanks to couples who got hitched soon after World War
II. More than 6.1 million couples married between 1946 and 1948,
paving the way for the baby boom. In 1948, 1.8 million marriages
took place, a number that would not be matched again until 1966.
(Harper, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
