<P>
   LIVE-NUDES _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Men, you owe J.P. Danko a
debt of gratitude. Night after hellish night, for three months he
endured a grueling blur of silicone, skimpy lingerie and surly
bouncers, all so that there might be an authoritative guide to the
highest-quality adult nightclub entertainment our nation has to
offer. The result: a light-hearted 160-page opus titled Live Nude
Girls ($14.95, St. Martin's Press). It's a practical,
tongue-in-cheek book that will bring a smirk or a dirty laugh of
recognition to anyone familiar with so-called gentlemen's clubs.
(Houck, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   NUDE-SIDE _ As in any business, those in the adult entertainment
industry have a sort of shorthand for various aspects of their
work. Author J.P. Danko gives us a peek in his book Live Nude
Girls: (List of phrases follows). (Houck, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   NUDE-SIDETWO _ Patrons at adult entertainment clubs fall neatly
into several categories, according to author J.P. Danko. (List
follows.) (Houck, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE _ ATLANTA -- Mergers, acquisitions, retro cars such as
the Volkswagen Beetle and the popularity of massive vehicles such
as the Lincoln Navigator have made for strange times in the auto
industry. To even casual observers, however, nothing seems stranger
than the idea of staid, safety-oriented Volvo introducing certified
head-turning cars. But that's the way it is with the Volvo C70
coupe and convertible, a pair of Swedish-built vehicles best
considered safe, swift, good-looking and pricey. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA -- Bob and Tony are in sales, and they
travel a great deal. Bob normally drives an extended-cab
four-wheel-drive pickup, Tony a two-door sport-utility vehicle.
Both are pretty big men. These two burly types would be taking an
almost 3,000-mile trip in a Volkswagen -- with a diesel engine, no
less. Their boss assured them the VW would be up to the task.
(Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MECHANIC _ ATLANTA _ Dave Grossman asked a question about fuel
octane. This question actually has a couple of answers. One
pertains to the octane requirements of the vehicle, and the other
addresses the vehicle's response to the lower octane fuel via the
engine's computerized management system. Before I get into the
``whys'' of octane, let's look inside the engine. (Carter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-ON-WOOD _ ATLANTA _ I come to sing the praises of a tool
more often considered hobbyist equipment than a serious woodworking
implement.
</P>
<P>
   It is the Dremel tool, the little hand-held rotary grinder that
used to be called the Moto-Tool, but has more recently been renamed
the MultiPro. It is, in many respects, the WD-40 of tools. (Warner,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL
</P>
<P>
   SEA-WORLD _ SAN ANTONIO, Texas _ It's hot, but the summer movies
have been so bad this year that it's not worth cooling off in a
theater, the malls are an air-conditioned bore and ice skating, no
matter how cold the ice, is for wimps. So where can you go to cool
off and simultaneously be entertained? I suggest you take the trip
to Sea World in San Antonio, Texas. (Kallenberg, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
