</P>
<P>
   CRITICALMASS _ For ``Saving Private Ryan.'' (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   WWII-FLICKS _ Steven Spielberg has brought back a long-lost
genre - the World War II movie. Saving Private Ryan is the story of
a GI squad sent in to save a young private whose three brothers
have already been killed in battle (shades of The Fighting
Sullivans). It's described as unflinchingly realistic in depicting
the bloody D-Day battle at Normandy. But listen up, soldier. A
World War II movie is still a World War II movie. And that means
we're going to meet that familiar platoon: young, scared,
ethnically balanced. And cliched. (List of other WWII movies
follows.) (Staff, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
