<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COX-2000-NUNN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NUNN TO HEAD COMPUTER CRISIS UNIT
 &HT;    c.1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Former Georgia Sen. Sam Nunn will head a new
private task force aimed at forging policy choices over the Year
2000 computer bug, which threatens to cause widespread disruptions
after Dec. 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
   The new unit, announced on Thursday, will be sponsored by the
Center for Strategic and International Studies, a think tank which
Nunn joined after leaving the Senate last year.
</P>
<P>
   The task force has scheduled risk-assessment meetings in early
October that will bring together officials from all levels of
government, as well as the private sector, to analyze the global
dimensions of the Year 2000 glitch.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
