<P>
   DELTA-MEETING _ (BRIEF) New York City? Delta Air Lines announces
its Oct. 22 annual shareholder meeting will be in the Big Apple,
ending the company's longstanding tradition of sticking close to
home. Delta has held all but one of its meetings in Monroe, La.,
the obscure city where it became an airline in 1930. In Monroe the
meeting is at a Holiday Inn; in New York it'll be at the Waldorf
Astoria. (Thurston, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
