<SLUG> BC-DUPRI-SIDE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Jermaine Dupri: On the record about ...
 &HT;    (EMBARGOED UNTIL JULY 26: DO NOT USE BEFORE THEN)
 &HT;    By Sonia Murray
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   His background
</P>
<P>
   Jermaine Dupri was born Jermaine Mauldin, the son of Michael and
Tina Mauldin, Sept. 23, 1972, in Asheville, N.C. They moved to
Atlanta when he was 3. When his parents divorced, Jermaine took his
mother's maiden name. (But his black and gray monogrammed towels
bear the initials JDM.)
</P>
<P>
   The woman in his life
</P>
<P>
   ``I've been in an off and on situation for like a while ... like
at least five years. Basically I just live like a bachelor. But
every man has got somebody that he always sees regardless if
they're single or not.''
</P>
<P>
   How he came up with Usher's triple-platinum `My Way'
</P>
<P>
   ``I did things like listen to him talk on the phone to girls. I
wanted Usher to sound on record like he sounded in real life. So I
studied his life, took him to strip clubs, I might have corrupted
him or whatever, but it had to all go together. It all went into
this image me and (LaFace co-president Antonio) L.A. (Reid) had for
Usher as this Bobby Brown kind of star.''
</P>
<P>
   What `1472' is
</P>
<P>
   J is the 10th letter in the alphabet, D is the fourth. Added
together you get 14, and '72 is the year Dupri was born. ``But it
means more than that,'' he explains. ``The whole concept behind my
record is 1472 is like a city that I basically feel I live in. It's
a world centered around myself that people enter into to change
their lives. Then the movie, `The City of 1472' (still in
development), will follow my record. And the idea for the movie is
pretty much like `The Wiz,' where I'm the Wizard of Oz and instead
of the city being filled with emeralds and whatever, mine is filled
with gold and platinum dreams.''
</P>
<P>
   In the works
</P>
<P>
   A Harlem World album, including Mase (``Feels So Good''), is due
in October, followed by the third release from the first female sn
between, Dupri plans to make time to work with one artist outside
his label, Whitney Houston.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
