</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    And the Emmy nominees are...
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the major nominees for the 1997-98 prime-time Emmy
awards. This year's telecast airs live Sept. 13 on NBC from the Los
Angeles Shrine Auditorium.
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama series: ``ER''; ``Law &AMP; Order''; ``NYPD Blue''; ``The
Practice''; ``The X-Files.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy series: ``Ally McBeal''; ``Frasier''; ``The Larry
Sanders Show''; ``Seinfeld''; ``3rd Rock From The Sun.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Miniseries: ``Armistead Maupin's More Tales of the City'';
``From the Earth to the Moon''; ``George Wallace''; ``Merlin'';
``Moby Dick.''
</P>
<P>
   -- TV movie: ``A Bright Shining Lie''; ``Don King: Only In
America''; ``Gia''; ``12 Angry Men''; ``What the Deaf Man Heard.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama actor: Andre Braugher, ``Homicide: Life on the
Street''; David Duchovny, ``The X-Files''; Anthony Edwards, ``ER'';
Dennis Franz, ``NYPD Blue''; Jimmy Smits, ``NYPD Blue.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama actress: Gillian Anderson, ``The X-Files''; Roma
Downey, ``Touched by an Angel''; Christine Lahti, ``Chicago Hope'';
Julianna Margulies, ``ER''; Jane Seymour, ``Dr. Quinn, Medicine
Woman.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy actor: Michael J. Fox, ``Spin City''; Kelsey Grammer,
``Frasier''; John Lithgow, ``3rd Rock From The Sun''; Paul Reiser,
``Mad About You''; Garry Shandling, ``The Larry Sanders Show.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy actress: Kirstie Alley, ``Veronica's Closet''; Ellen
DeGeneres, ``Ellen''; Jenna Elfman, ``Dharma &AMP; Greg''; Calista
Flockhart, ``Ally McBeal''; Helen Hunt, ``Mad About You''; Patricia
Richardson, ``Home Improvement.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Miniseries, movie actor: Jack Lemmon, ``12 Angry Men''; Sam
Neill, ``Merlin''; Ving Rhames, ``Don King: Only in America''; Gary
Sinise, ``George Wallace''; Patrick Stewart, ``Moby Dick.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Miniseries, movie actress: Ellen Barkin, ``Before Women Had
Wings''; Jamie Lee Curtis, ``Nicholas' Gift''; Judy Davis, ``The
Echo of Thunder''; Olympia Dukakis, ``Armistead Maupin's More Tales
of the City''; Angelina Jolie, ``Gia''; Sigourney Weaver, ``Snow
White: A Tale of Terror.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama supporting actor: Gordon Clapp, ``NYPD Blue''; Hector
Elizondo, ``Chicago Hope''; Steven Hill, ``Law &AMP; Order''; Eriq La
Salle, ``ER''; Noah Wyle, ``ER.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama supporting actress: Kim Delaney, ``NYPD Blue''; Laura
Innes, ``ER''; Camryn Manheim, ``The Practice''; Della Reese,
``Touched by an Angel''; Gloria Reuben, ``ER.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy supporting actor: Jason Alexander, ``Seinfeld''; Phil
Hartman, ``NewsRadio''; David Hyde Pierce, ``Frasier''; Jeffrey
Tambor, ``The Larry Sanders Show''; Rip Torn, ``The Larry Sanders
Show.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy supporting actress: Christine Baranski, ``Cybill'';
Kristen Johnston, ``3rd Rock From The Sun''; Lisa Kudrow,
``Friends''; Jane Leeves, ``Frasier''; Julia Louis-Dreyfus,
``Seinfeld.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Miniseries, movie supporting actor: Hume Cronyn, ``12 Angry
Men''; Gregory Peck, ``Moby Dick''; George C. Scott, ``12 Angry
Men''; Martin Short, ``Merlin''; J.T. Walsh, ``Hope.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Miniseries, movie supporting actress: Helena Bonham Carter,
``Merlin''; Julie Harris, ``Ellen Foster''; Judith Ivey, ``What the
Deaf Man Heard''; Angelina Jolie, ``George Wallace''; Mare
Winningham, ``George Wallace.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama directing: Mark Tinker, ``Brooklyn South''; Bill
D'Elia, ``Chicago Hope''; Thomas Schlamme, ``ER''; Paris Barclay,
``NYPD Blue''; Chris Carter, ``The X-Files.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy directing: Allan Arkush, ``Ally McBeal''; James
Frawley, ``Ally McBeal''; James Burrows, ``Dharma &AMP; Greg''; Todd
Holland, ``The Larry Sanders Show''; Terry Hughes, ``3rd Rock From
The Sun.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Miniseries, movie directing: John Herzfeld, ``Don King: Only
In America''; Tom Hanks, ``From the Earth to the Moon''; John
Frankenheimer, ``George Wallace''; Steve Barron, ``Merlin'';
William Friedkin, ``12 Angry Men.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Variety, musical performance: Garth Brooks, ``Garth Live From
Central Park''; Michael Crawford, ``Michael Crawford In Concert'';
Billy Crystal, ``The 70th Annual Academy Awards''; Jay Leno, ``The
Tonight Show With Jay Leno''; David Letterman, ``The Late Show With
David Letterman''; Tracey Ullman, ``Tracey Takes On ...''
</P>
<P>
   -- Variety, music, comedy series: ``Dennis Miller Live''; ``The
Late Show With David Letterman''; ``Politically Incorrect With Bill
Maher''; ``The Tonight Show With Jay Leno''; ``Tracey Takes On
...''
</P>
<P>
   -- Animated program: ``Cow And Chicken''; ``Dexter's
Laboratory''; ``King of the Hill''; ``The Simpsons''; ``South
Park.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Comedy writing: ``Ally McBeal: Theme of Life''; ``Ellen:
Emma''; ``Frasier: The Ski Lodge''; ``The Larry Sanders Show:
Putting The 'Gay' Back In Litigation''; ``The Larry Sanders Show:
Flip.''
</P>
<P>
   -- Drama writing: ``Homicide: Life on the Street: The Subway'';
``NYPD Blue: Lost Israel''; NYPD Blue: Lost Israel, Part II'';
``The Practice: Betrayal''; ``The X-Files: The Post-Modern
Prometheus.''
</P>
