<P>
   INGRAM-MICRO-COMPUTERS (Memphis, Tenn.) _ Ingram Micro, a
computer wholesaler, is at the heart of a total reinvention of the
way products are made, distributed and sold. It is Ingram that
pieces together made-to-order computers for H-P, IBM and Compaq _
all of them in one plant in Memphis _ and then sends them to end
customers, regardless of the retailer that sold them. Such
new-style middlemen are transforming other industries, too. By Saul
Hansell. Graphic. &QL; 
