<SLUG> BC-LINCOLN-PICKUP-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BED TIME FOR LINCOLN? PICKUP WOULD BE PLUSH 
</HEADLINE>
  (th) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Figuring that well-heeled Americans would like a truck with
limousine pretensions, Lincoln Mercury is considering whether to
offer the ultimate pickup.
</P>
<P>
   Informally called the Blackwood, the truck might be based on the
big Ford Super Duty. It would combine the opulence of the Navigator
sport utility with myriad luxury features and genuine wood in the
pickup bed. It would sell for $40,000 to $50,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``We won't rule out anything,'' a Ford product development
executive said.
</P>
<P>
   Strong demand for Navigators has emboldened Ford's truck
developers. An even larger sport utility, the Excursion, will take
on General Motors' Suburban next year.
</P>
<P>
   ``We reap substantial benefits by doing the unexpected,'' the
executive said. ``Even wilder ideas are under consideration.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
